What person's name is associated with the fracture shown below? <image 1> 

A. Monteggia
B. Bennett
C. Jones
D. Colle

We refer to Wikipedia articles on clinical knowledge for help. The image shows a Bennett fracture, which is a fracture of the base of the first metacarpal bone (the bone leading to the thumb). This type of fracture is named after Edward H. Bennett, an Irish surgeon who first described it in 1882.

Therefore, the answer is B.
